    {
      "version": "0.2.0",
      "date": "2026-07-08",
      "icon": "👥",
      "title": "Share your work",
      "summary": "Invite teammates to any note or collection, give them Editor or Viewer access, and edit together — changes sync live, end-to-end encrypted, with the relay never seeing your content. Viewers are now truly read-only.",
      "body": [
        {
          "kind": "h1",
          "text": "Sharing & permissions"
        },
        {
          "kind": "li",
          "text": [
            {
              "text": "Share",
              "marks": ["bold"]
            },
            {
              "text": " any note or collection from its "
            },
            {
              "text": "⋯ menu",
              "marks": ["highlight"]
            },
            {
              "text": " — add a teammate by their invite code or by name, and see everyone with access at a glance."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "li",
          "text": [
            {
              "text": "Roles",
              "marks": ["bold"]
            },
            {
              "text": " — grant "
            },
            {
              "text": "Editor",
              "marks": ["highlight"]
            },
            {
              "text": " (can change) or "
            },
            {
              "text": "Viewer",
              "marks": ["highlight"]
            },
            {
              "text": " (read-only) access, and revoke it any time. A Viewer's edits are now blocked at the data layer, not just hidden — so read-only means read-only."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "li",
          "text": [
            {
              "text": "Live editing",
              "marks": ["bold"]
            },
            {
              "text": " — once shared, edits flow both ways in real time, converging cleanly even after you've both been offline."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "callout",
          "icon": "🔒",
          "text": [
            {
              "text": "Still yours alone. ",
              "marks": ["bold"]
            },
            {
              "text": "Everything is encrypted per-entity on your devices; the sync relay only ever sees ciphertext, never your content or who you're working with."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "p",
          "text": [
            {
              "text": "One note on removing access: revoking a teammate stops future grants and hides the entity from them, but does not yet rotate the encryption key. A removed collaborator who already has the key can still read edits made after they're removed. Full rotate-on-revoke (new key, re-shared only with remaining members) is coming in a follow-up."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "callout",
          "icon": "🔄",
          "text": [
            {
              "text": "Update in place. ",
              "marks": ["bold"]
            },
            {
              "text": "Existing installs update from "
            },
            {
              "text": "Settings → Updates",
              "marks": ["highlight"]
            },
            {
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
